---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bahrain Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/bahrain/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
  { title: 'Qatar for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/qatar' },
  { title: 'Saudi Arabia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/saudi-arabia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bahrainFit', header: 'Bahrain Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BHD 140-200/mo', bahrainFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BHD 165-235/mo', bahrainFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BHD 130-185/mo', bahrainFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BHD 120-170/mo', bahrainFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Bahrain Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'BHD 40-120/mo', bahrainFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BHD 130-200', annual: 'BHD 1,560-2,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BHD 180-270', annual: 'BHD 2,160-3,240' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BHD 240-360', annual: 'BHD 2,880-4,320' },
  { category: 'Bahrain Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: 'Nominal fees' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'BHD 15-40/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bahrain 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Bahrain. Island kingdom, relaxed Gulf lifestyle, good healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bahrain"
  subheadline="Bahrain offers the most relaxed Gulf lifestyle—island living, good healthcare, cultural tolerance, and the Golden Residency for property investors and retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/bahrain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Bahrain</h2>
  <p>
    Bahrain is the Gulf's most relaxed destination—island nation with cosmopolitan atmosphere, cultural tolerance, and established expat community. The Golden Residency program specifically welcomes retirees. While smaller than neighbors, Bahrain offers Gulf lifestyle without strictness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Manama provides capital living with modern amenities. Amwaj Islands and other areas offer waterfront lifestyle. The island is small (765 km²)—everything is accessible within 30 minutes. Rich history (Dilmun civilization), pearling heritage, and Formula 1 add character.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good; modern private facilities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English very widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BHD 800-1,800/month (~$2,100-4,800); moderate for Gulf</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Desert; hot humid summers (40°C+)</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax; no capital gains tax</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Most relaxed Gulf state; tolerant atmosphere</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Bahrain's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Bahrain has good healthcare—Salmaniya Medical Complex is the main public hospital. Private hospitals like Royal Bahrain Hospital, American Mission Hospital, and Bahrain Specialist Hospital provide quality care. Many doctors are Western-trained. Standard is good for the region.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is subsidized for residents (small fees). Expats typically use private hospitals with insurance. For complex cases, Dubai (1 hour flight) or further afield may be needed. Overall quality is good for routine and moderate complexity care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Small Island Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bahrain is small—some highly specialized treatments may not be available locally. Dubai and Saudi Arabia are nearby for complex cases. International insurance with evacuation coverage is valuable. However, for most senior healthcare needs, Bahrain's private hospitals are adequate.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Bahrain offers attractive options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Golden Residency Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Bahrain's Golden Residency specifically targets retirees and investors. For retirees: monthly income of BHD 2,000+ (~$5,300) from pension or investments qualifies. 10-year renewable residence for retiree and family.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Investment</h3>
  <p>
    Buying property worth BHD 50,000+ (~$133,000) in designated areas grants residence. Can be combined with Golden Residency. Amwaj Islands and other developments welcome foreign ownership.
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Sponsorship</h3>
  <p>
    Bahrain allows self-sponsorship for individuals with sufficient income. Flexible option for those not qualifying for Golden Residency but with financial independence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Bahrain:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mandatory:</strong> Health insurance required for residence permits</li>
    <li><strong>Golden Residency:</strong> Insurance proof needed for application</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage level:</strong> Must meet Bahrain minimum standards</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Typically accepted and preferred for seniors</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Bahrain</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is recommended for seniors—local Bahraini insurers often have age restrictions. Major providers (Cigna, BUPA, Allianz) are recognized and meet requirements. Include Dubai coverage for potential complex care needs. Bahrain's private healthcare is good for most needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Bahrain, international providers work best:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Bahrain</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Gulf network, recognized in Bahrain</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Middle East focus, regional expertise</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Gulf pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well for Bahrain.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Bahrain are moderate for the Gulf region:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local private care is affordable; high deductible works</li>
    <li><strong>Gulf-only coverage:</strong> Excluding Europe/US reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations BHD 15-30; easy cash payment</li>
    <li><strong>Dubai access:</strong> Include UAE for complex care options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,200/month pension (exceeds BHD 2,000). Golden Residency applicant.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa and coverage. Uses Royal Bahrain Hospital. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~BHD 165/month (~£350). Tax-free pension; relaxed island lifestyle.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Property Investor, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Buying BHD 100,000 apartment in Amwaj Islands. $3,500/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Property residence. BUPA Global comprehensive. Dubai access for complex care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~BHD 250/month (~$660). Waterfront retirement; good healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Indian Professional Couple, Both 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Former Bahrain workers. Combined savings + pension. Returning for retirement.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Self-sponsorship. Now Health for both. Familiar with Bahrain system.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~BHD 270/month combined (~$715). Known environment; established networks.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How relaxed is Bahrain compared to other Gulf states?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Most relaxed in the Gulf. Alcohol is available in hotels, restaurants, and licensed stores. Dress code is liberal by Gulf standards. Mixed-gender socializing is normal. Churches and temples operate openly. Ramadan requires some public discretion but much less strict than neighbors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the Golden Residency process like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Relatively straightforward—proof of income (pension statements, bank statements), health insurance, passport copies. Processing takes 2-4 weeks typically. Valid 10 years, renewable. Includes spouse and dependents. One of the Gulf's most retiree-friendly programs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bahrain expensive to live in?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate by Gulf standards—cheaper than UAE or Qatar. Housing is more affordable than Dubai. Dining and entertainment are reasonable. Alcohol is expensive. A comfortable lifestyle is possible on $3,000-4,000/month. For Gulf tax-free living, it offers good value.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the heat and humidity?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Summers are challenging—40°C+ with high humidity (island effect). June-September is difficult for outdoor activity. Everything is air-conditioned. Many expats travel during peak summer. Winters (November-March) are pleasant—20-25°C, perfect for outdoor life.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers recognized for Bahrain Golden Residency.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Bahraini authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
